      "message": "[warning] Line 398: This now treats every read error except EAGAIN/EWOULDBLOCK as device removal. `read(2)` can also fail with `EINTR` when interrupted by a signal, which should not disconnect a valid HID device. Please retry on `EINTR` before falling through to `removeDevice()`.\n\n```suggestion\n            if (n \u003c 0) {\n                if (errno \u003d\u003d EINTR)\n                    continue;\n                if (errno \u003d\u003d EAGAIN || errno \u003d\u003d EWOULDBLOCK)\n                    break; // no more data for now\n            }\n```",
